{"lemma":"ساقِطٌ","slug":"ساقِطٌ","root":"س.ق.ط","root_slug":"س-ق-ط","root_link":"/words/roots/س-ق-ط","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"ساقِط","root":"سقط","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["adj","noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":7},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n20096"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B3%D8%A7%D9%82%D9%90%D8%B7%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"fallen, falling, dropping"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"vile, disreputable"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"annulled, abolished, void"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"incident (of light)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"lowlife"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"caducous"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"caduca, decidua"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Derived from the active participle of the verb سَقَطَ (saqaṭa, “to fall”)."},"ipa":["/saː.qitˤ/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n20096","headword_ar":"سَاقِطٌ","root":"sqT","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Falling; falling down; dropping; dropping down; tumbling down;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saquwTN","text_ar":"سَقُوطٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, K;) which latter is both masc. and fem. (M, TA.) ―         -b2-  ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAqiTapN","text_ar":"سَاقِطَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[its fem., as an epithet in which the quality of a subst. predominates,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A fruit that falls before maturity:"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sawaAqiTu","text_ar":"سَوَاقِطُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": which also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what falls from palm-trees:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"branches that fall;"},{"kind":"text","text":"not fruits. (Mgh.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa saAqiTN fiY yadihi","text_ar":"هُوَ سَاقِطٌ فِى يَدِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masoquwTN","text_ar":"مَسْقُوطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laAqiTapN","text_ar":"لَاقِطَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"likul~i saAqiTapK","text_ar":"لِكُلِّ سَاقِطَةٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"For every saying that falls from one, there is a person who will take it up:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for every word that falls from the mouth of the speaker, there is a person who will hear it and pick it up and publish it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"a prov., relating to the guarding of the tongue: (TA:) the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":"in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lAqTp","text_ar":"لاقطة"},{"kind":"text","text":"is either to give intensiveness to the meaning or for the purpose of assimilation. (Msb.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino HarK","text_ar":"مِنْ حَرٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sawaAqiTu","text_ar":"سَوَاقِطُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Fallings of heat."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA.) [See 1, near the end of the paragraph.] ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAqiTN","text_ar":"سَاقِطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Hanging down; pendent; pendulous:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suq~aATN","text_ar":"سُقَّاطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b7-  [And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Tottering"},{"kind":"text","text":"by reason of age.] You say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ayoxN saAqiTN kibarFA","text_ar":"شَيْخٌ سَاقِطٌ كِبَرًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An old man tottering by reason of age"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"drhm","text_ar":"درهم"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b8-  Also (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Low, ignoble, base, vile,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mean, in respect of the deeds or qualities of his ancestors, and of himself;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh;) and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAqiTapN","text_ar":"سَاقِطَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) or, (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in respect of the deeds or qualities of his ancestors, and of his race;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAqiTapN","text_ar":"سَاقِطَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) (assumed tropical:)  one who is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not reckoned among the better,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"best, class of young men;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saqoTN","text_ar":"سَقْطٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) (tropical:)  one"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who is,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"remains, behind,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the rear of, other men:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K:) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"obscure, unnoted, reputeless,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of no reputation:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suq~aATN","text_ar":"سُقَّاطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, TA) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saqoTaY","text_ar":"سَقْطَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"siqaATN","text_ar":"سِقَاطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which last is like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"niyaAmN","text_ar":"نِيَامٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naAy^imN","text_ar":"نَايِمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suqaTaA='u","text_ar":"سُقَطَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [by rule a pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saqiyTN","text_ar":"سَقِيطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which see in what follows,] and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sawaAqiTu","text_ar":"سَوَاقِطُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAqiTapN","text_ar":"سَاقِطَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) The epithets"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAqiTN maAqiTN laAqiTN","text_ar":"سَاقِطٌ مَاقِطٌ لَاقِطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"are used together, as signifying (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Low, ignoble, base, vile,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mean;"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied to a man; as is said in the L: or, accord. to the O, [and the S in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mqT","text_ar":"مقط"},{"kind":"text","text":",] the Arabs say, in reviling,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN saAqiTu bonu maAqiTi boni laAqiTK","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ سَاقِطُ بْنُ مَاقِطِ بْنِ لَاقِطٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one is a slave of a slave of a slave of a freedman, son of a slave of a slave of a freedman, son of a slave of a freedman;"},{"kind":"text","text":"the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sAqT","text_ar":"ساقط"},{"kind":"text","text":"being the slave of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mAqT","text_ar":"ماقط"},{"kind":"text","text":", and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mAqT","text_ar":"ماقط"},{"kind":"text","text":"being the slave of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lAqT","text_ar":"لاقط"},{"kind":"text","text":", and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lAqT","text_ar":"لاقط"},{"kind":"text","text":"being the slave of the freedman. (TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suq~aATu Aln~aAsi","text_ar":"سُقَّاطُ النَّاسِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies, accord. to IAar, (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The refuse, rabble,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lowest"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"basest"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"meanest sort, of mankind,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of people;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"x$r","text_ar":"خشر"},{"kind":"text","text":";) as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~aAsi","text_ar":"النَّاسِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saqaTu","text_ar":"سَقَطُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~aAsi","text_ar":"النَّاسِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asoqaATu","text_ar":"اَسْقَاطُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", as being likened to those articles of a tent or house which are termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saqaTN","text_ar":"سَقَطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v.: (Lh, M:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suq~aATu Aljunodi","text_ar":"سُقَّاطُ الجُنْدِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Soldiers of whom no account is made."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAqiTapN","text_ar":"سَاقِطَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, L, TA,) in the K ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saqiyTapN","text_ar":"سَقِيطَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", but this is a mistake, (TA,) or, applied to a man, only used when immediately followed by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laqiyTapN","text_ar":"لَقِيطَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lqT","text_ar":"لقط"},{"kind":"text","text":",) also signifies (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Deficient in intellect,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intelligence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"understanding;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, L, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saqiyTN","text_ar":"سَقِيطٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Ez-Zejjájee, M, L, K;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saqiyTap","text_ar":"سَقِيطَة","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the fem. of the latter; (M, L, TA;) and signifies also, applied to a woman, (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Low, ignoble, base, vile,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mean,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and stupid."},{"kind":"text","text":"(So in some copies of the S, and in the TA.) You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlfiEoli","text_ar":"الفِعْلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa saAqiTapu","text_ar":"هُوَ سَاقِطَةُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is mean in conduct:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one of whose actions no account is made"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b9-  Also, [as signifying (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Vile, mean,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"paltry,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] applied to a thing: (TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lqT","text_ar":"لقط"},{"kind":"text","text":":) [a thing] (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"falling short of the due,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"just, mean."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wsT","text_ar":"وسط"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b10-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAqiTu","text_ar":"سَاقِطُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~adi","text_ar":"الشَّدِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  A horse"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that runs interruptedly."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA.) ―         -b11-  ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sawaAqiTu","text_ar":"سَوَاقِطُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Persons who come to El-Yemámeh to bring thence for themselves provisions of dates."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K, TA.) ―         -b12-  And ↓ this last word, (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Small, low mountains,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as though"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cleaving to the ground."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["Msb","TA","S","K","M","Mgh","Lh","L"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}